ranked first in three states and in the fourth, Sinaloa, the group of "Homicide 
and lesions caused intentionally by another person" ranked first.
CONCLUSIONS: This work highlights the importance of the YLPP with economic loss 
ponderation index to discriminate death causes among states in a region with 
apparently homogeneous mortality.

